{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πτύω</b>, <br /> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.697, etc.: \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>future</i> πτύσω [ῠ] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προρρητικόν” 2.40 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πτύσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Morb.” 1.28: \">Refs</a>]<i>aorist</i> ἔπτῠσα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 22, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 653, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>perfect</i> ἔπτῠκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Sextus Empiricus Philosophus “adversus Mathematicos” 8.252, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 10.374, 11.281:\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] —<i>passive</i>, <i>future</i> πτυσθήσομαι (ἀνα-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 9.686, 15.700, (ἐμ-) NT.Luke.18.32 \">NT</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἐπτύσθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ νούσων” 1.28 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist 2</i> <i>participle</i> πτυέντα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Epid.” 2.3.4 \">Refs</a>]. [ῡ in <i>present</i> and <i>imperfect</i>; later <i>Epic dialect</i> have ῠ in <i>imperfect</i> before a short syllable, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 10.171 \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>], but mostly in compounds, (ἀνα-) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 2.570, (ἀπο-) 4.925, (ἐξ-) 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 24.19 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; ῠ always in <i>aorist</i>): —<b>spit out</b> or <b>up</b>, αἷμα Il.[same place], [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἄρθρων ἐμβολῆς” 49 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>absolutely</i>, <b>spit</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.99, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.1.42: with _dative_, πτύσας προσώπῳ\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <b>spat</b> in his face, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1232. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of the sea, <b>disgorge, cast out</b>, με.. τηλόσ᾽ ἀπὸ.. ἠϊόνος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 7.283 (1st c.AD: Leonidas Alexandrinus Epigrammaticus), compare 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 5.596: _metaphorically_, στοργὰν ἔπτυσας εἰς ἀνέμους “Anthologia Graeca” 7.468 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus): _absolutely_, ἐπ᾽ ἀϊόνι πτύοντα, of waves, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.133; ἱστὸς ὄλισθεν εἰς ἅλα πτύσας \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<b>with a splash,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anthologia Graeca 9.290 (1st c.AD: Philippus Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.b</b></Level4> of fish, <b>spawn</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Babrius Fabularum Scriptor 6.8. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__2.c</b></Level4> proverbial, πρὶν πτύσαι 'before you can say Jack Robinson', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus “Περικειρομένη” 202. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, πτύσας <b>with loathing</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 653; ἰδεῖν ῥᾷόν ἐστι καὶ πτύσαι 4th c.BC: Epicrates Comicus 3.20. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> εἰς κόλπον π., to avert a bad omen, disarm magic, etc., which was done three times, ὡς μὴ βασκανθῶ δὲ τρὶς εἰς ἐμὸν ἔπτυσα κόλπον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 6.39, compare 20.11; φρίξας εἰς κόλπον πτύσαι 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 16.15, compare 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Nav.” 15, etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ὑπὸ κόλπον π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 12.229 (2nd c.AD: Strato Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>promote the flow of spittle</b>, of certain wines, in <i>passive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης” 2.52 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. (Cf. Gothic <i>speiwan</i> 'spit', Latin <i>spuo</i>, etc.)","strongNumber":"G4429","accentedUnicode":"πτύω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1609","matchingForm":"ἐκπτύω","stepTransliteration":"ekptuō","gloss":"to spit out","_zh_tw_Gloss":"厭棄","_es_Gloss":"escupir ","_zh_Gloss":"厌弃"},{"strongNumber":"G1716","matchingForm":"ἐμπτύω","stepTransliteration":"emptuō","gloss":"to spit on/at","_zh_tw_Gloss":"吐唾沫","_es_Gloss":"escupir en ","_zh_Gloss":"吐唾沫"},{"strongNumber":"G4427","matchingForm":"πτύσμα","stepTransliteration":"ptusma","gloss":"saliva","_zh_tw_Gloss":"唾沫","_es_Gloss":"saliva","_zh_Gloss":"唾沫"}],"shortDef":"to spit (saliva)","mediumDef":"to spit (saliva) <br /><b>to spit, spit out,</b> <ref='Mrk.7.33; 8:23'>Mk. 7:33; 8:23</ref>; <ref='Jhn.9.6'>Jn. 9:6</ref>","stepGloss":"to spit","stepTransliteration":"ptuō","count":3,"_es_Definition":"escupir","_zh_tw_Definition":"吐唾沫, 吐出來 (可 7:33, 8:23; 約 9:6)","_zh_Definition":"吐唾沫, 吐出来 (可 7:33, 8:23; 约 9:6)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"nhổ; nhổ nước bọt.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"吐唾沫","_es_Gloss":"escupir","_zh_Gloss":"吐唾沫"}]}